BIB                 10         18
TITLE      Cross section for absorption of gamma-rays by sulphur
            nuclei in the region of the giant dipole resonance.
AUTHOR     (B.S.Dolbilkin,A.I.Isakov,V.I.Korin,L.E.Lazareva,
            F.A.Nikolaev)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSLEB)
REFERENCE  (J,SNP,8,626,1969)
            English translation of YF,8,1080,1968.
           (J,YF,8,1080,1968)
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
FACILITY   (SYNCH,4RUSLEB)
SAMPLE     Natural sulphur mixture (32S - 95.02 %, 34S - 4.22 %).
METHOD     (EXTB,SITA)
DETECTOR   (BPAIR) 9-channel magnetic pair spectrometer.
HISTORY    (20110927C) Data were compiled at the Russia MSU SINP
            CDFE by V.Varlamov.
           (20140225A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: REFERENCE.
           (20260411A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: REFERENCE,
            CORRECTION -> ANALYSIS, REACTION, STATUS.
ENDBIB              18
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           21
SUBENT        M0824002   20260411   20260518   20260518       M145
BIB                  5         13
REACTION   (16-S-32(G,TOT),,SIG)
           Nuclear photoabsorption cross-section as difference
            between total photon absorption cross section and
            atomic absorption cross section.
ANALYSIS   Photoabsorption cross   section   was   obtained   by
            subtraction of the atomic absorption  cross  section
            from  the  experimentally measured sum of atomic and
            nuclear absorption cross sections.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Root-mean-squared uncertainties.
STATUS     (CURVE,,B.S.Dolbilkin+,J,SNP,8,626,1969)
            Data from Fig. 1.
HISTORY    (20260411A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: REACTION,
            STATUS.
